      <body>

		<!-- AGAIN, UNIQUE ID PLUS 3-DIGIT PAGE # IN THE FOLLOWING -->
         <pb facs="uva.00206.001" xml:id="leaf001r" type="recto"/>

		       <!-- IF THE MANUSCRIPT IS SOMETHING OTHER THAN ONE POEM    -->
		       <!-- (FOR EXAMPLE, "MULTIPLE POEMS" OR "POEM NOTES"), YOU  --> 
		       <!-- MUST INSERT A <div1> HERE WITH THE APPROPRIATE 	     -->
		       <!-- "type" ATTRIBUTE 					           -->
         <lg
              >

		<!-- FOR THE LINE BELOW, IF NO TITLE IS WRITTEN ON THE MS,   -->
		<!-- ALTER THE "type" ATTRIBUTE TO READ "main-derived". ONLY -->  
		<!-- INCLUDE THE REND ATTRIBUTE IF THE TITLE IS WRITTEN ON   -->
		<!-- THE MANUSCRIPT AND IS UNDERLINED.  			       -->
            <head type="main-authorial" rend="underline">
</head>

		          <!-- THE FOLLOWING <l> AND  TAGS JUST INDICATE THAT  -->
		          <!-- THE CONTENT OF THE MANUSCRIPT POEM BEGINS HERE. 	  -->
		          <!-- PLEASE FOLLOW PROPER PROCEDURES TO ENCODE THE        -->
		          <!-- SPECIFICS OF YOUR MANUSCRIPT 			  -->
	               
            <l> </l>

            <l>
                <lb/> 
                <lb/>
            </l>

            <l>
               <note type="authorial">35</note>
               <note type="authorial"
                     place="left">tr down</note>
               <del rend="hashmark">
                  <transpose anchored="no">O my reached hands!O fruit for my hungry soul! O hanging everywhere on unseen branches!</transpose>
               </del>
            </l>
	           <l>
               O me, man of slack faith<lb/>
               so long! Man <del rend="overstrike">of</del>
               <lb/>
               
                  <del rend="overwrite">s</del>
               <lb/>
               Standing aloof<del rend="overstrike">no long</del>
               <lb/>
               Denying portions so long!<lb/>
            </l>
	           <l>
               Me with mole's eyes, not<lb/>
               yet risen to buoyancy<lb/>
               and vision—not yet free,<lb/>
            </l>
	           <l>
               Me, just aware <del rend="overstrike">this</del>today<lb/>
               of<del rend="overstrike">the</del> compact all:<lb/>
               diffused <subst>
                     <rdg varSeq="1">
                        <del rend="overstrike">right</del>
                     </rdg>
                     <rdg varSeq="2">
                        <add rend="unmarked" place="supralinear">truth.</add>
                     </rdg>
                  </subst>
               <lb/>
            </l>


            <pb facs="uva.00206.002" xml:id="leaf002r" type="recto"/>
            <gap reason="cut away"/>
            <l>
               
                  <subst>
                     <rdg varSeq="1">
                        <del rend="overstrike">Because I discover</del>
                     </rdg>
                     <rdg varSeq="2">
                        <add rend="unmarked" place="supralinear">Disover to=day</add>
                     </rdg>
                  </subst>there is<lb/>
               no lie, or form of lie,<lb/>
               and can be none, but<lb/>
               
                  <del rend="overstrike">is</del>is<add rend="insertion" place="supralinear">
                     <del rend="overstrike">stands</del>grows</add>as inevitably<lb/>
	              
                  <del rend="overstrike">after</del>
                  <add rend="unmarked" place="supralinear">upon</add>itself, or as<lb/>
               any<del rend="overstrike">law</del>law of the<lb/>
               earth, or any natural<lb/>
               production of the earth.<lb/>
            </l>
	           <l>
               (This is a curious saying,<lb/>
               and may not be realized<lb/>
               immediately—But it must<lb/>
               be realized.)<lb/>
            </l>
	           <l>
               I feel in myself that I represent<lb/>
               falsehood equally with the<lb/>
               rest—and that the universe<lb/>
               does.)<lb/>
            </l>

            <pb facs="uva.00206.003" xml:id="leaf003v" type="verso"/>
            <l>
               
                  <addSpan type="pasteon" place="over" to="a1"/>
                  <delSpan rend="hashmark" to="d1" />I thought <del rend="overstrike">the </del>
                  <subst>
                     <rdg varSeq="1">
                        <del rend="overwrite">t</del>
                     </rdg>
                     <rdg>
                        <add rend="overwrite" place="over">T</add>
                     </rdg>
                  </subst>ruth sublime—<lb/>
               But how far more sub:<lb/>
               lime it is than I thought!<lb/>
            </l>
            <l>
               Now it is proved to me by itself, and it is proved<lb/>
               <gap reason="cut away"/>
            </l>

            <pb facs="uva.00206.004" xml:id="leaf04v" type="recto"/>
            <l>
               Where has failed a perfect<lb/>
               return<add rend="insertion" place="supralinear">indifferent of lies or the truth?</add>
               <lb/>
            </l>
            <l>
               Is it upon the ground, or<lb/>
               in water or fire, or in<lb/>
               the spirit of man, or<lb/>
               in the meat and blood?<lb/>
            </l>
            <l>
               Meditating among liars, and<lb/>
               retreating sternly into<lb/>
               myself, I see that there<lb/>
               are really no liars or<lb/>
               lies, after all,<lb/>
            </l>
            <l>
               
                  <subst>
                     <rdg varSeq="1">
                        <del rend="overstrike">But</del>
                     </rdg>
                     <rdg varSeq="2">
                        <add rend="unmarked" place="supralinear">And</add>
                     </rdg>
                  </subst>that nothing fails its<lb/>
               perfect return—and<lb/>
               that what are called<lb/>
               lies are perfect returns,<lb/>
            </l>
            <l>
               And that each thing exactly<lb/>
               represents itself and what<lb/>
               has preceded it,<lb/>
            </l>
            <anchor xml:id="a1"/>
            <anchor xml:id="d1"/>

            <pb facs="uva.00206.005" xml:id="leaf05v" type="verso"/>
            <l>
               And that the truth includes<lb/>
               all, and is compact,<lb/>
               just as much as space<lb/>
               is compact,<lb/>
            </l>
            <l>
               And that there is no flaw<lb/>
               or<subst>
                     <rdg varSeq="1">
                        <del rend="overstrike">speak</del>
                     </rdg>
                     <rdg varSeq="2">
                        <add rend="unmarked" place="supralinear">vacuum</add>
                     </rdg>
                  </subst>in the amount<lb/>
               of the truth—but that all is<lb/>
               truth, without exception,<lb/>
            </l>
            <l>
               And henceforth I will go <delSpan rend="hashmark" to="d1" />
                  <subst>
                     <rdg varSeq="1">
                        <del rend="overstrike">look</del>
                     </rdg>
                     <rdg varSeq="2">
                        <add rend="unmarked" place="supralinear">trust</add>
                     </rdg>
                  </subst>
                  <del rend="overstrike">jubilant</del>
                  <subst>
                     <rdg varSeq="1">
                        <del rend="overstrike">of all</del>
                     </rdg>
                     <rdg varSeq="2">
                        <add rend="unmarked" place="supralinear">in whatever</add>
                     </rdg>
                  </subst>
               <lb/>
               
                  <subst>
                     <rdg varSeq="1">
                        <del rend="overstrike">though</del>
                     </rdg>
                     <rdg varSeq="2">
                        <add rend="insertion" place="supralinear">I hear or see,</add>
                     </rdg>
                  </subst>and sing and<lb/>
               laugh, and decry nothing.<lb/>
               <anchor xml:id="d1"/>
               celebrate<del rend="overstrike">all</del>anything I<lb/>
               see or am, and sing and<lb/>
               laugh, and deny nothing.—<lb/>
            </l>
	
	
         </lg>
